──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
B.1 — shadow_gap (Simpson's-paradox C-channel) is structurally zero.
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Reading from the sweep above: shadow_gap = ±0.0000 across ALL five
bias values, even when reproduction bias is dialed to 4.0 and 88.9%
of all replicators are cooperators.

WHY: shadow_gap = global_A − mean_local_A is a Simpson's-paradox
detector. It fires only when LARGER groups have systematically
DIFFERENT compositions than smaller groups. That requires variable
group SIZE correlated with group COMPOSITION.

In this Moran/fixed-population system:
  • Cell mass (A+B) lives in [K/2, K] ≈ [20, 40].
  • Internal kinetics (k_A·A vs k_B·B) drift composition without
    coupling it to total mass.
  • Therefore mass and composition are approximately independent.
  • Therefore global_A and mean_local_A are equal by construction.

shadow_gap is a Wright–Fisher diagnostic. Importing it into Moran
systems gives a guaranteed null reading regardless of selection
strength. This is the formal version of the "shadow_gap = 0" result
that surprised SwarmGPT in the first round — now diagnosed.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
B.2 — Both correlation-based channels collapse at strong selection.
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Look at the sweep again, focused on the metric values rather than
the rescue ratio:

    bias=0.00:  S=+0.051, C_off=+0.039  (selection mild, signal high)
    bias=4.00:  S=+0.006, C_off=-0.004  (selection strong, signal ~0)

This is the OPPOSITE of what a good MLS detector should do. The
strongest selection regime registers as no selection.

WHY: both metrics are correlations across the within-population
axis (across cells at one time point). Strong selection drives
within-population homogenization. Composition std collapses from
0.19 (bias=0) to 0.09 (bias=4). With low variance in composition,
ANY correlation against composition has no signal to find.

CONSEQUENCE: SwarmGPT's "shadow_gap > ε" criterion would falsely
report the most strongly selected populations as showing the LEAST
multi-level selection. The metric is sensitive to the DERIVATIVE of
selection, not to its LEVEL.

This is not a bug in C47H's wiring — it is a property of any
within-population correlation-based detector applied at a strong-
selection equilibrium.

