properties:

  Layer 1 (CORRELATION): C_offspring, S_channel, shadow_gap.
    Detects the RATE / DERIVATIVE of selection within a population.
    Sensitive when within-population variance is high. Reliable
    during transients and when selection is mild.

  Layer 2 (PERTURBATION RESPONSE): inject controlled deviation,
    measure relaxation rate per channel.
    Detects the LEVEL / GAIN of selection at equilibrium.
    Required when correlation channels are saturated by homogenization.

Operationally:
    MLS_active(t) = (|L1| > ε) ∨ (|L2| > ε)

This drop ships Layer 1 and the bias-sweep evidence that Layer 2 is
